  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We present a case study of team of three students who designed a babyGPT model to generate Marvel-like screenplays (see Figure 5 for examples of outputs from the model).",
    "The team identified that the latest Marvel films were of lower quality and decided to build a screenplay generator that, trained on the scripts of their favored films, would generate new scripts.",
    "In doing so, they engaged with data practices (Olari & Romeike, 2024) such as understanding a task and defining success criteria.",
    "While building their model, the team collected data, controlled the quality of the data, prepared the data by tokenizing it and evaluated the performance of their model.",
    "Engaging in these practices iteratively provided opportunities for students to consider how data quality impacts model outputs and to participate in complex discussions about copyright, authorship, and attribution."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In doing so, they engaged with data practices (Olari & Romeike, 2024) such as understanding a task and defining success criteria."
  ]
